cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.HC 

This paper describes a method for training a soft robotic hand to perform dexterous manipulation tasks using reinforcement learning and object-centric demonstrations. The paper focuses on the robotics aspect of the research, which suggests that it is most likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. However, the use of reinforcement learning and neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves computer vision techniques for object recognition, which suggests that it could belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the use of human demonstrations and the focus on making the robotic hand more accessible and user-friendly suggests that it could belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
